about.description:
lorem is a generator for random text that looks like Latin for Python 3.3+.
It is pure Python code with no dependencies.
about.summary: Generator for random text that looks like Latin

name: lorem
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "lorem" %}
{% set version = "0.1.1" %}
{% set sha256 = "785f4109a241fc2891e59705e85d065f6e6d3ed6ad91750a8cb54d4f3e59d934" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  number: 1001
  skip: True  # [py<34]
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - lorem

about:
  home: https://github.com/sfischer13/python-lorem
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'Generator for random text that looks like Latin'

  description: |
    lorem is a generator for random text that looks like Latin for Python 3.3+.
    It is pure Python code with no dependencies.
  dev_url: https://github.com/sfischer13/python-lorem

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - sfischer13
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.6.14
